In his dream-encounter with the seventh question=2C Kenny is visited by th=
e rooster once more=2C who goes on to grill the boy in a rapid-fire sessio=
n of question-and-answer. =E2=80=9CWhat is an only goat?=E2=80=9D the roos=
ter demands=2C and Kenny volleys back=2C =E2=80=9Ca lonely goat=E2=80=9D;=
 =E2=80=9CWhat is a very narrow escape?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CWhen somebody al=
most stops loving you.=E2=80=9D On and on they go=2C question by question=
=2C until the rooster poses the final one.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0060287896/braipick-20?mc_cid=3D24a=
a1ea22b&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

=E2=80=9CDo you always want what you think you want?=E2=80=9D

Kenny thought for as long as he could. =E2=80=9CI think I don=E2=80=99t kn=
ow=2C=E2=80=9D he said sadly.

=E2=80=9CThink hard=2C=E2=80=9D said the rooster.

Kenny thought hard and then smiled.

=E2=80=9CI know=2C=E2=80=9D he said.

=E2=80=9CWhat?=E2=80=9D asked the rooster eagerly.

=E2=80=9CI thought I wanted to live in the garden with the moon on one sid=
e and the sun on the other=2C but I really don=E2=80=99t.=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=9CYou=E2=80=99ve answered all the questions=2C=E2=80=9D the rooster=
 shouted=2C =E2=80=9Cand you can have whatever you want.=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=9CI wish=2C=E2=80=9D Kenny said slowly=2C =E2=80=9C=E2=80=94I wish=
 I had a horse=2C and a ship with an extra room for a friend.=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=9CYou can have them=2C=E2=80=9D said the rooster.

=E2=80=9CWhen?=E2=80=9D cried Kenny. =E2=80=9CWhere are they?=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=9CThere=2C=E2=80=9D said the rooster=2C pointing out the window. Ke=
nny pressed his nose against the glass.

=E2=80=9CAcross the street?=E2=80=9D he asked.

=E2=80=9CFurther than that=2C=E2=80=9D said the rooster. Kenny stood on ti=
p-toe.

=E2=80=9CI can=E2=80=99t see any further than that=2C=E2=80=9D he shouted.

The rooster hopped on Kenny=E2=80=99s shoulder.

=E2=80=9CI see them=2C=E2=80=9D he whispered=2C =E2=80=9Cpast the houses=
=2C over the bridge=2C near a mountain on the edge of the ocean.=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=9Cthat=E2=80=99s too far=2C=E2=80=9D said Kenny and he looked away.

=E2=80=9CBut you=E2=80=99er halfway there=2C=E2=80=9D the rooster said.

In the dark=2C Kenny=E2=80=99s eyes grew big. =E2=80=9CHow did I get so fa=
r?=E2=80=9D he asked.

=E2=80=9CYou made a wish=2C=E2=80=9D said the rooster=2C =E2=80=9Cand a wi=
sh is halfway to wherever you want to go.=E2=80=9D

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0060287896/braipick-20?mc_cid=3D24a=
a1ea22b&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

Kenny=E2=80=99s Window (http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0060287896/=
braipick-20?mc_cid=3D24aa1ea22b&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) is a tender and immens=
ely thoughtful gem in its entirety. Complement it with Sendak=E2=80=99s ra=
rest and most formative art (https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/06/10/maur=
ice-sendak-william-blake-songs-of-innocence-1967/?mc_cid=3D24aa1ea22b&mc_e=
id=3D[UNIQID]) =2C his wisdom on art=2C storytelling=2C and life (https:/=
/www.brainpickings.org/2013/07/18/maurice-sendak-yale?mc_cid=3D24aa1ea22b&=
mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) from the 1971 class he taught at Yale=2C and his littl=
e-known and lovely posters celebrating libraries and the joy of reading (h=
ttps://www.brainpickings.org/2013/09/03/maurice-sendak-posters-reading-boo=
ks/?mc_cid=3D24aa1ea22b&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C then join me in supporting=
 (https://www.rosenbach.org/donate?mc_cid=3D24aa1ea22b&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID])=
 the wonderful Rosenbach Museum & Library=2C which Sendak entrusted with h=
is legacy (https://www.rosenbach.org/learn/collections/maurice-sendak-coll=
ection?mc_cid=3D24aa1ea22b&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) .


