s? Has he not the entire world within himself?</p></blockquote><p style=3D=
"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #262626;=
font-family: Georgia=2C serif;font-size: 15px;line-height: 175%;text-align=
: left;">Half a century before Agnes Martin=E2=80=99s memorable observatio=
n that <a href=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=
=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3D3a306992bd&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-we=
bkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #C33737;text=
-decoration: underline;">=E2=80=9Cwe all have the same inner life [but] t=
he artist has to recognize what it is=2C=E2=80=9D</a> Hesse adds:</p><bloc=
kquote style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;=
display: block;-webkit-margin-before: 0;-webkit-margin-after: 0;-webkit-ma=
rgin-start: 40px;-webkit-margin-end: 0px;"><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-a=
djust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=
=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;"><img s=
rc=3D"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1/images/2e292=
385-dc1c-4cfe-b95e-845f6f98c2ec.png" align=3D"left" style=3D"-ms-interpola=
tion-mode: bicubic;border: 0;height: auto;line-height: 100%;outline: none;=
text-decoration: none;padding: 5px 30px 10px 0px;display: inline;width: 50=
px!important;">Whoever remained permanently at this stage would not read a=
ny more=2C but no one does remain permanently at this stage. But whoever i=
s not acquainted with this stage is a poor=2C an immature reader. He does=
 not know that all the poetry and all the philosophy in the world lie with=
in him too=2C that he greatest poet drew from no other source than the one=
 each of us has within his own being. For just once in your life remain fo=
r an hour=2C a day at the third stage=2C the stage of not-reading-any-more=
=2E You will thereafter (it=E2=80=99s so easy to slip back) be that much bet=
ter a reader=2C that much better a listener and interpreter of everything=
 written. Stand just once at the stage where the stone by the road means a=
s much to you as Goethe and Tolstoy=2C you will thereafter gain from Goeth=
e=2C Tolstoy=2C and all poets infinitely more value=2C more sap and honey=
=2C more affirmation of life and of yourself than ever before. For the wor=
ks of Goethe are not Goethe and the volumes of Dostoevsky are not Dostoevs=
ky=2C they are only an attempt=2C a dubious and never successful attempt=
=2C to conjure up the many-voiced multitudinous world of which he was the=
 central point.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%=
;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #262626;font-family: Georgia=2C serif;f=
ont-size: 15px;line-height: 175%;text-align: left;">Hesse likens this type=
 of reading to a <a href=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.list-manage2.com/trac=
k/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3D01f47612d2&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" sty=
le=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #C3=
3737;text-decoration: underline;">dream</a>=2C or perhaps to what Stephen=
 King has termed <a href=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.list-manage2.com/trac=
k/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3Dafd5a1235b&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" sty=
le=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #C3=
3737;text-decoration: underline;">=E2=80=9Ccreative sleep.=E2=80=9D</a> Dr=
eaming transmogrifies the raw material of reality=2C gathered in our wakin=
g life=2C into fanciful creations of the consciousness set free from the c=
onstraints of reality. Similarly=2C this type of reading uses the actual t=
ext on the page as raw material for the imaginative meanderings of the min=
d. Hesse writes:</p><blockquote style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-m=
s-text-size-adjust: 100%;display: block;-webkit-margin-before: 0;-webkit-m=
argin-after: 0;-webkit-margin-start: 40px;-webkit-margin-end: 0px;"><p sty=
le=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #80=
8080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;te=
xt-align: left;"><img src=3D"https://gallery.mailchimp.com/13eb080d8a31547=
7042e0d5b1/images/2e292385-dc1c-4cfe-b95e-845f6f98c2ec.png" align=3D"left"=
 style=3D"-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;border: 0;height: auto;line-heig=
ht: 100%;outline: none;text-decoration: none;padding: 5px 30px 10px 0px;di=
splay: inline;width: 50px!important;">A dream is the opening through which=
 you see into the content of your soul=2C and this content is the world=2C=
 no more and no less than the world=2C the whole world from your birth up=
 to today=2C from Homer to Heinrich Mann=2C from Japan to Gibraltar=2C fro=
m Sirius to the Earth=2C from Red Riding Hood to Bergson. =E2=80=94 And to=
 the extent that your attempt to write down your dream is related to the w=
orld that embraces that dream=2C so the work of an author is related to wh=
at he tired to say.</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text=
-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-si=
ze: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;">[=E2=80=A6]</p><p style=3D"=
-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;f=
ont-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-ali=
gn: left;">Without having recognized this=2C be it only a single time=2C i=
n all its infinite fullness and inexhaustible significance=2C you stand ha=
ndicapped before every poet and thinker=2C you take for the whole what is=
 a small part=2C you believe in interpretations that barely touch the surf=
ace.</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 1=
00%;color: #808080;font-family: Arial=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-h=
eight: 170%;text-align: left;">[=E2=80=A6]</p><p style=3D"-webkit-text-si=
ze-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #808080;font-family: Ari=
al=2C Sans-serif;font-size: 14px;line-height: 170%;text-align: left;">The=
 third stage at which you are most yourself will put an end to your readin=
g=2C will dissolve poetry=2C will dissolve art=2C will dissolve world hist=
ory. And yet unless you intuitively know this stage=2C you will never read=
 any book=2C any science or art except as a schoolboy reads his grammar.</=
p></blockquote><p style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-ad=
just: 100%;color: #262626;font-family: Georgia=2C serif;font-size: 15px;li=
ne-height: 175%;text-align: left;">Hesse=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"http://brain=
pickings.us2.list-manage2.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=
=3D4c3d9dd9d2&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms=
-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #C33737;text-decoration: underline;"><stron=
g><em>My Belief</em></strong></a>=2C it bears repeating=2C is a transcende=
nt read in its entirety. Complement this particular fragment with Virginia=
 Woolf on <a href=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?=
u=3D13eb080d8a315477042e0d5b1&id=3D111220daff&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-w=
ebkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #C33737;tex=
t-decoration: underline;">how to read a book</a>=2C Patti Smith on <a href=
=3D"http://brainpickings.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315=
477042e0d5b1&id=3D1b8f51a60e&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-a=
djust: 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #C33737;text-decoration: und=
erline;">the two types of masterpieces</a>=2C C.S. Lewis on <a href=3D"htt=
p://brainpickings.us2.list-manage1.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a315477042=
e0d5b1&id=3D9b33181813&e=3Da5eb5cdf67" style=3D"-webkit-text-size-adjust:=
 100%;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #C33737;text-decoration: underline=
;">why we read</a>=2C and a very old Robert Graves=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"ht=
tp://brainpickings.us2.list-manage2.com/track/click?u=3D13eb080d8a31547704=
